dataset.title: Chicago Catholic Churches, 1940
dataset.description:
This map shows the distribution of catholic churches in Chicago, in 1940. Originally produced by Wesley Akin Hotchkiss. The number of persons per church field was created by repeating the legend item into the attribute table, and the number of churches field was created by counting the number of dots that fall into each polygon. The map was created as a combination of Chicago community areas and Illinois municipalities map, that fit the locations and names in both shapefiles and map legends. The birds eye view map was distorted to fit the NAD 83 Illinois East projection system, and therefore, the further away from the center of the map, the more distorted the georeferencing is. The georeferencing method is the third order polynomial, which was enough to identify the polygons, but not to estimate with certainty the location of the dots places on the original map. Due to that difference, the dot representing the churches were counted, not placed on the vector map.

Call number: G4104.C6E42 1940.H61. https://catalog.lib.uchicago.edu/vufind/Record/8007705

Map Collection, Regenstein Library, University of Chicago

Originally produced by Wesley Akin Hotchkiss.

dataset.title: Chicago Police Districts 1998
dataset.description: This file gives 1998 boundaries of the districts used by the Chicago Police Department. It is derived largely from the maps at the Police Department's Website. Author of shapefile: Christopher Siciliano. Shapefile name is poldist.shp

dataset.title: Chicago City Limits
dataset.description: This file corrects several problems in the original TIGER/line files, notably the inclusion of parts of Lake Michigan within the city limits, and the numerous irregularities that are a function of the way the TIGER/line files were created. This file will consequently not line up with TIGER/line streets or tracts; it will line up with the 1992 ward boundary file. Its author is Christopher Siciliano.

dataset.title: World Borders 1925
dataset.description: First-order political boundaries in approximately January 1925. Accompanying dbf file shows status of each political unit. Disputed areas generally have their own polygons. Author of file is Sam Brown. Name of the shapefile is WorldBorders1925.shp

dataset.title: Chicago Wards 1986
dataset.description: This is the ward map that preceded the 1992 map. The file was generated largely from voting district boundaries (which are numbered by ward) and may consequently contain some minor errors. Christopher Siciliano did a considerable amount of cleaning up of this file. Name of the shapefile is ward1986.shp

dataset.title: Chicago Wards 1992
dataset.description: This map was current from 1992 until 1998, when litigation forced some boundary changes. This file contains accurate straight lines in some places where the corresponding street files have inaccurate crooked lines. The author of this boundary file is Christopher Siciliano. It was edited very slightly in 2001 by George Stachokas.

dataset.title: Chicago Wards 1998
dataset.description: This is the ward map for Chicago that was in effect between 1998 and early 2003. The file was derived from the Tiger 1998 voting district file. George Stachokas has edited the file, altering some of the boundaries to make them more closely resemble the boundaries shown in the city of Chicago's published ward maps. Name of the shapefile is ward1998.shp
